# ats-platform — Cursor rules

npm workspace **`ats-platform`**: `apps/*`, `packages/*`. Human reference: **`docs/PROJECT_STRUCTURE.md`**.

## Monorepo map

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `apps/candidate-portal` | Next.js — public candidate UI — **port 3000** |
| `apps/backoffice` | Next.js — staff back office — **port 3001** |
| `apps/api` | Hono HTTP API — **port 4000** (`PORT`) |
| `packages/db` | **Only** Prisma schema + migrations + shared client |
| `packages/ui`, `types`, `utils`, `auth`, `validators`, `config` | Shared libraries (`@ats-platform/*`) |
| `docs/` | Specs, API dictionary, static markup (`markup/candidate-portal`, `markup/backoffice`) — **not** runtime imports |

Run all apps: **`npm run dev:all`** (repo root).

## Where to put code

### Next.js (`candidate-portal`, `backoffice`)

| Location | Use for |
|----------|---------|
| `src/app/` | App Router routes, layouts, `globals.css` |
| `src/components/` | Reusable presentational UI (shared within that app) |
| `src/features/` | Vertical slices (jobs, auth, etc.); pages orchestrate features |
| `src/lib/` | App-only helpers; **`prisma.ts`** re-exports `prisma` from **`@ats-platform/db`** |

- Do **not** add a second Prisma schema inside an app.
- Shared React primitives go in **`@ats-platform/ui`** when used by both web apps.

### HTTP API (`apps/api`)

| Location | Use for |
|----------|---------|
| `src/index.ts` | Bootstrap Hono, global middleware, `serve()` |
| `src/routes/` | Wiring: `registerRoutes()`, health/demo, mount prefixes |
| `src/middlewares/` | Cross-cutting (logging, CORS, auth guards) |
| `src/lib/` | API-local helpers; **`prisma.ts`** re-export from **`@ats-platform/db`** |
| `src/modules/<domain>/` | Domain routes (Hono sub-app per area: `auth`, `jobs`, `candidates`, `applications`, `interviews`, `users`, `notifications`) |

Register new domain routes in **`src/routes/index.ts`** with `app.route("/prefix", module)`.

### Database & Prisma

- **Single source of truth:** `packages/db/prisma/schema.prisma` and `packages/db/prisma/migrations/`.
- **Never** copy or duplicate `schema.prisma` under `apps/` or `docs/`.
- Migrations and `prisma generate` run via **`@ats-platform/db`** from root: `npm run db:migrate`, `npm run db:generate` (also **`postinstall`**).
- App code imports: `import { prisma } from "@ats-platform/db"` (or via each app’s `src/lib/prisma.ts`).
- **`db:create`** reads **`DATABASE_URL`** from **repo root `.env`**.

### Shared packages (`packages/*`)

- **`@ats-platform/validators`** — Zod schemas for API and optional Next server code.
- **`@ats-platform/types`** — DTOs and shared TS types (no DB client here).
- **`@ats-platform/auth`** — session/JWT/RBAC abstractions (no app-specific UI).

**Dependency direction:** `apps/*` → `packages/*` only. Packages do **not** depend on apps.

## Environment

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| Repo root `.env` | `DATABASE_URL` for Prisma CLI and `db:create` |
| `apps/candidate-portal/.env.local` | Next + `DATABASE_URL` if using Prisma in server code |
| `apps/backoffice/.env.local` | Same |
| `apps/api` | `PORT`; `DATABASE_URL` when using Prisma |

## Conventions

- Match existing naming: **`@ats-platform/<name>`** workspace packages.
- API `tsconfig` uses **`moduleResolution: "bundler"`** — avoid unnecessary `.js` extensions in local TS imports unless policy changes.
- Specs and REST contracts live under **`docs/specification/`**; keep implementation aligned with **`docs/specification/api/`** and **`API_Dictionary.md`** when changing HTTP behavior.
- Prefer focused changes; avoid unrelated refactors in the same PR.

## Documentation to cite

- **`docs/PROJECT_STRUCTURE.md`** — full tree, route map, scripts.
- **`docs/specification/db-schema.md`** — relational model (companion to Prisma schema).
